[{"id":"VH908622","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VH906858.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Based on the line graph, which of the following statements about church attendance in 1972 is true?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH908622_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<p class=\"title_line passage-title\">CHURCH ATTENDANCE IN THE UNITED STATES, 1972-2010</p>\n</div>\n<img alt=\"The figure presents a line graph titled “Church Attendance in the United States, 1972 through 2010.” The horizontal axis is labeled “Year” and the years 1972 through 2010, in increments of 2, are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled “Religious Attendance” and the percentages 0 through 50, in increments of 10%, are indicated. The right side of the figure has the label “Figures for 2010,” and indicates the percentage of attendance in the following four categories: 1. “43.5%, Rarely/Never.” 2. “30.3%, Weekly.” 3. “16.0%, Monthly.” 4. “10.3%, Yearly.” The data represented in the line graph, by year, are as follows. Note that all values are approximate. 1972: 28% Rarely/Never, 41% Weekly, 16% Monthly, 14% Yearly. 1980: 35% Rarely/Never, 36% Weekly, 15% Monthly, 15% Yearly. 1990: 35% Rarely/Never, 35% Weekly, 18% Monthly, 13% Yearly. 2000: 40% Rarely/Never, 30% Weekly, 15% Monthly, 13% Yearly.\" height=\"246\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH906858.g03.png\" width=\"600\" /></div>\n\n<p class=\"attribution author\">Source: General Social Survey, 2010.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">In 1972, about 30% of people surveyed reported attending church monthly or less.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">In 1972, more people surveyed reported attending church weekly than reported attending rarely or never.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">In 1972, most people surveyed reported attending church yearly.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">In 1972, more people surveyed reported attending church yearly than reported attending weekly.</p>"],"answer":1}]